#: ../../../trace/rv/hybrid_automata.rst:133
msgid ""
"This model imposes that the time between when a task is enqueued (it becomes "
"runnable) and when the task gets to run must be lower than a certain "
"threshold. A failure in this model means that the task is starving. One "
"problem in using guards on the edges in this case is that the model will not "
"report a failure until the ``switch_in`` event occurs. This means that, "
"according to the model, it is valid for the task never to run."
msgstr ""

